ime genres did not simply mirror urban settings and social realities, but actively produced and circulated new ideas about the shifting surfaces of public culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCities and towns in motion pictures. 0aCity and town life in motion pictures. 0aCrime filmszUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 4aCriminology : Criminology. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aHistory : History. 4aSociology : Urban Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847122840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438471228423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438471228/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles